com.desafio.ponto.service.persistence

Class PontoMarcacoesUtil

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.desafio.ponto.service.persistence.PontoMarcacoesUtil

  • @ProviderType
public class PontoMarcacoesUtil
extends java.lang.Object
    The persistence utility for the ponto marcacoes service. This utility wraps PontoMarcacoesPersistenceImpl and provides direct access to the database for CRUD operations. This utility should only be used by the service layer, as it must operate within a transaction. Never access this utility in a JSP, controller, model, or other front-end class.

    Caching information and settings can be found in portal.properties

    Author:
    Peterson Morais
    See Also:
    PontoMarcacoesPersistence, PontoMarcacoesPersistenceImpl

      • findByFindByPisData

        public static java.util.List<PontoMarcacoes> findByFindByPisData(long Pis,
                                                                 long Data,
                                                                 int start,
                                                                 int end)
        Returns a range of all the ponto marcacoeses where Pis = ? and Data = ?.

        Useful when paginating results. Returns a maximum of end - start instances. start and end are not primary keys, they are indexes in the result set. Thus, 0 refers to the first result in the set. Setting both start and end to QueryUtil#ALL_POS will return the full result set. If orderByComparator is specified, then the query will include the given ORDER BY logic. If orderByComparator is absent and pagination is required (start and end are not QueryUtil#ALL_POS), then the query will include the default ORDER BY logic from PontoMarcacoesModelImpl. If both orderByComparator and pagination are absent, for performance reasons, the query will not have an ORDER BY clause and the returned result set will be sorted on by the primary key in an ascending order.

        Parameters:
        Pis - the pis
        Data - the data
        start - the lower bound of the range of ponto marcacoeses
        end - the upper bound of the range of ponto marcacoeses (not inclusive)
        Returns:
        the range of matching ponto marcacoeses

      • findAll

        public static java.util.List<PontoMarcacoes> findAll(int start,
                                                     int end)
        Returns a range of all the ponto marcacoeses.

        Useful when paginating results. Returns a maximum of end - start instances. start and end are not primary keys, they are indexes in the result set. Thus, 0 refers to the first result in the set. Setting both start and end to QueryUtil#ALL_POS will return the full result set. If orderByComparator is specified, then the query will include the given ORDER BY logic. If orderByComparator is absent and pagination is required (start and end are not QueryUtil#ALL_POS), then the query will include the default ORDER BY logic from PontoMarcacoesModelImpl. If both orderByComparator and pagination are absent, for performance reasons, the query will not have an ORDER BY clause and the returned result set will be sorted on by the primary key in an ascending order.

        Parameters:
        start - the lower bound of the range of ponto marcacoeses
        end - the upper bound of the range of ponto marcacoeses (not inclusive)
        Returns:
        the range of ponto marcacoeses
